The incidence of severe reduced amniotic fluid volume in the 2nd trimester is rare, but causes a dramatic rise in morbidity and mortality of the fetus. Since Gembruch and Hansmann [12] reported about their experiences with the diagnostic and therapeutic approach of amnioinfusion in 1988 there followed sporadic reports about amnioinfusion by other investigators. In the following the experiences with diagnostic and therapeutic amnioinfusion in the 2nd trimester and the technique will be disscussed.  
